title: Spain challenges Catalonia independence referendum in constitutional court
description:
The Spanish government has moved to crush Catalonia's plans for an independence referendum, with the country's state prosecutor's office saying it will present criminal charges to members of the Catalan parliament who voted in favour of the ballot.

The local authority, which is controlled by pro-independence parties, on Wednesday approved legislation to allow next month’s bitterly disputed vote to go ahead, however, Prime Minister Mariano Rajoy said that the referendum was illegal and poses an …
